The Seven Habits of Highly Effective People, first published in 1989, as a self-help book written by Stephen R. Covey. It has sold over 15 million copies in 38 languages. This video illustrations based on the book produced by the award-winning team that brought you In Search of Excellence,

this new program as seen on PBS will provide you with valuable insights into how the 7 Habits work on an individual level, with organizations and entire communities. Through testimonials, you can enhance your principle-centered awareness and reenergize your work force around the value-based approach of the 7 Habits. In addition to seeing the 7 Habits at work, you will be able to see how your organization can improve key management skills like teamwork and leadership through the application of these habits.
